sql:
SELECT retweets 
FROM tweets 
WHERE tweet_id = '0';

SELECT retweet_count
FROM tweets
ORDER BY retweet_count DESC;

external_knowledge:
Engagement score is a measure of how interactive a tweet is, often based on the number of likes, comments, retweets, etc. it receives; 
A high engagement score indicates a popular or influential user;
Average sentiment score indicates the general sentiment or attitude conveyed by a user's tweets, often measured through natural language processing techniques;
Top users are those with the highest average engagement scores, indicating their ability to interact with their audience effectively.
